assemblage.p:
Suppose that \Delta ABC has sides of length a, b, and c. Then the area of \Delta ABC is given by
    A=\sqrt{s(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)}
    where s=\dfrac{a+b+c}{2} is the semiperimeter.
